Key Match Events: The Thunder opened a six-point lead in the third quarter when Shai Gilgeous-Alexander made a three-pointer.
The Thunder dominated the second quarter, outscoring the Rockets 41-20 to take a 75-51 lead at halftime.
Others: The Thunder shot 51.1% from the field and made 20 of 23 free throws.
Dillon Brooks scored 17 points for the Rockets, who shot just 43.3% from the field.
